{
  "id": "quotient-rule",
  "name": "Quotient Rule for Derivatives",
  "latex": "\\frac{d}{dx}[\\frac{f(x)}{g(x)}] = \\frac{f'(x)g(x) - f(x)g'(x)}{[g(x)]^2}",
  "explanation": "The quotient rule finds the derivative of a quotient (division) of two functions. The formula is: derivative of top times bottom, minus top times derivative of bottom, all divided by bottom squared. Remember: 'low d-high minus high d-low, over low squared' helps memorize this rule.",
  "examples": [
    {
      "problem": "Find the derivative of f(x) = x²/(x + 1)",
      "solution": "f'(x) = (x² + 2x)/(x + 1)²",
      "steps": [
        "f(x) = x², g(x) = x + 1",
        "f'(x) = 2x, g'(x) = 1",
        "Quotient rule:",
        "f'(x) = [2x(x + 1) - x²(1)]/(x + 1)²",
        "= [2x² + 2x - x²]/(x + 1)²",
        "= (x² + 2x)/(x + 1)²"
      ]
    },
    {
      "problem": "Differentiate h(x) = (2x + 3)/(x - 1)",
      "solution": "h'(x) = -5/(x - 1)²",
      "steps": [
        "f(x) = 2x + 3, g(x) = x - 1",
        "f'(x) = 2, g'(x) = 1",
        "h'(x) = [2(x - 1) - (2x + 3)(1)]/(x - 1)²",
        "= [2x - 2 - 2x - 3]/(x - 1)²",
        "= -5/(x - 1)²"
      ]
    }
  ],
